<DOC><DOCNO> AP881012-0149 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-12-88 1426EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Nigeria     10-12 0129</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Nigeria,0132</SECOND><HEAD>President Announces New Anti-Corruption Drive</HEAD><DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Nigeria's military leader on Wednesdayannounced a new campaign aimed at weeding out corrupt officials intop government circles and commercial banks.   Gen. Ibrahim Babangida, who seized power from another militaryleader in 1985, would not detail what form the campaign would take.   In his comments to the country's attorney generals, Babangidasaid corrupt officials would be punished and that the Ministry ofJustice was working on new decrees and regulations for the campaign.   The president said he particularly was concerned about personalenrichment by government officials and bankers. He said if it wasnot curbed now, corruption could be permanently entrenched by thetime his military government handed power over to a civiliangovernment in 1992.</TEXT></DOC>